From 9529125aa38fea0d925f439ee28b46242b598a8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philippe Simons <simons.philippe@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 10:47:17 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] input: touchscreen: add Synaptics DSX driver for TDDI chips

Add the Synaptics DSX touchscreen driver, ported to kernel 7.0.
This driver supports Synaptics TDDI (Touch and Display Driver
Integration) chips like the TD4310 which require the DSX protocol
rather than the mainline RMI4 driver.

The mainline RMI4 driver cannot activate touch on TDDI chips because
the touch digitizer requires DSX-specific initialization that the
RMI4 protocol layer does not provide.

Ported from SynapticsHostSW/synaptics_dsx_release_p3 with:
- Legacy GPIO API converted to gpiod
- early_suspend removed (uses PM ops)
- I2C probe/remove signatures updated for kernel 6.3+
- VLAs replaced with dynamic allocation
- KERNEL_ABOVE ifdefs removed

Signed-off-by: Philippe Simons <simons.philippe@gmail.com>
---
